oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Red clover for silage: management impacts on ensilability indices in the second season after sowing
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: O'Kiely, P.
Black, A.D.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Pasture and forage crops
Post harvest management and techniques
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This experiment quantified the impacts of cultivar, companion grass, harvest schedule and N fertiliser on herbage ensilability at each of four harvests in the second year after sowing.
oai_dc:dc.dc:identifier: O'Kiely, P. and Black, A.D. (2008) Red clover for silage: management impacts on ensilability indices in the second season after sowing. In: Proceedings of the Agricultural Research Forum, p. 110.
